 "logTail": [
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"What name did I give? When they pulled me out.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "You"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"None. You gave none. Three days I have had nothing to call you, and neither have you.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Sōan"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Nothing comes.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Genemon does not look surprised. He looks down and writes, and reads it back as he writes, aloud and once.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "One man, name unknown. Taken at the weir. Fed, three days. Condition, poor; hands, good.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"When he can stand, he rakes. The kitchen wants water before it wants anything.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "He goes. Sōan opens his ledger again, where his thumb kept the place.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"How long was I in the river?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "You"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"That I can't write down. Three days here, fevered. Before that, ask the river.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Sōan"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Someone on the bank said a god hid me.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "You"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Kamikakushi. The valley says it of every man the river takes and every child who runs off. Let them say it; it comforts them and costs you nothing. What took you was water.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Sōan"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Where is this?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "You"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"The Kurosawa house — the estate, or what answers to the word. This is my sickroom, off the outer court, and you will be out of it by tomorrow. I need the mat.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Sōan"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"The work. Point me at it.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "You"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Can you stand? Then the rake is by the door, and the well is past the kitchen. Water first — the kitchen never has enough. Come back when something bleeds.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Sōan"
  },
  {
   "channel": "milestone",
   "text": "Perk unlocked — The Well Yoke: a load the shoulders carry before it is asked. (+1 STR / −1 LUCK)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Standing. Day four; the book said three, so the book gains a line. I am Genemon, steward of the Kurosawa — what this house still has, I count, and you are counted in it now. Ask what you must; the entry is not closed.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "(You say nothing, and take up the rake by the door.)",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Written: no answer given; rake taken, unasked. Work entered before words — the book counts that fastest, and luck not at all.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "milestone",
   "text": "Perk unlocked — Hands Before Words: A steady quickness that answers with work — trusting to no luck. (+1 SPD / −1 LUCK)",
   "count": 1
  }
